  "text": "We managed to obtain 4,876 DEGs base on the transcription profile in TCGA dataset, out of which 3,453 genes were upregulated and 1,423 downregulated. The DEGs were presented in Supplementary Material S1. The KEGG analysis ( Figure 1 ) indicated that the genes were mainly involved in PI3K−Akt and MAPK signaling pathway, which are pivotal in the regulation of immune responses [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Specific IRGs were identified with intersection of the immune-related genes and DEGs in BLCA. As shown in Figure 2 , we identified 120 upregulated, and 140 downregulated BLCA-specific IRGs.",
